fields.name: Ebirr Project
fields.description: eBIRR is a mobile money platform in Ethiopia that facilitates digital transactions, including payments, transfers, and withdrawals. Integrating eBIRR with an application or system involves connecting to the eBIRR switch, which acts as an intermediary for processing financial transactions securely and efficiently.

fields.name: Design and Initiate
fields.description: The Design and Initiate phase is the foundation of integrating Mastercard with a payment switch, ensuring a structured approach for seamless transaction processing. This phase involves defining system architecture, compliance requirements, and technical specifications before implementation begins.

fields.name: Implementation and Configuration
fields.description: Integrating Mastercard with a payment switch involves configuring the necessary protocols, security measures, and transaction processing flows to enable seamless communication between the Mastercard network and the financial institution�s switch. This ensures that card-based transactions are securely routed, authorized, and settled in compliance with Mastercard�s regulations.

fields.name: MTF offline testing
fields.description: Mastercard Test Facility (MTF) is a simulation environment that enables financial institutions and payment processors to test their Mastercard transaction processing capabilities before going live. MTF Offline Testing allows institutions to validate their switch integration without direct connectivity to the Mastercard network, ensuring compliance with Mastercard�s transaction processing standards.

fields.name: Certification phase
fields.description: The Mastercard Certification Phase is the final step before going live, where financial institutions, processors, and payment switches must pass a series of compliance tests to ensure proper integration with Mastercard�s network. This phase verifies that the switch can handle transactions securely, accurately, and in accordance with Mastercard�s ISO 8583 message specifications and security standards.

fields.name: Pilot test
fields.description: The Mastercard Pilot Test is the final real-world testing phase before full-scale production. This phase ensures that the switch, acquiring/issuing bank, and Mastercard network work seamlessly under live conditions with a limited number of real transactions. The pilot phase is crucial for identifying and resolving any issues before a full rollout.

fields.name: Go Live
fields.description: The Go-Live phase is the final stage in the Mastercard integration process, where the payment switch, acquiring/issuing bank, and Mastercard network transition from testing to full production. This phase involves monitoring real transactions, ensuring system stability, and addressing any unexpected issues promptly.

fields.name: Initiation and  Planning
fields.description: This phase involves defining the business and technical requirements for integrating eBIRR with your system. It ensures that all stakeholders understand the scope and objectives before development begins.

fields.name: Development and API Integration
fields.description: This phase focuses on implementing the core functionalities of the eBIRR switch integration, including API configuration and transaction processing logic.

fields.name: Testing and Quality Assurance
fields.description: This phase involves rigorous testing to ensure the system functions as expected and is secure before going live.

fields.name: User Acceptance Testing  and Certification
fields.description: Before going live, the system must be tested by real users and certified by eBIRR.

fields.name: Go Live and Post Deployment Monitoring
fields.description: Once certified, the integration is deployed to the live environment, and ongoing monitoring begins.

fields.name: Initiate a discussion session
fields.description: Initiate a discussion session with the Mastercard project implementor.

fields.name: Simulator License query
fields.description: A Simulator License Query is the process of obtaining, validating, and activating the necessary licensing for a Mastercard simulator. This license is required to use Mastercard�s testing environment for transaction simulations, certification, and compliance verification before going live.

fields.name: Define business requirements and objectives
fields.description:
Identify the core objectives of integrating eBIRR (e.g., seamless digital payments, improved transaction tracking, automated reconciliation).
Gather input from stakeholders, including business, finance, and IT teams, to define key use cases.
Determine the expected transaction volume, user types, and security considerations.
Document functional and non-functional requirements, ensuring alignment with business goals.

fields.name: API Access and  Documentation
fields.description: Establish communication with eBIRR, review API documentation, understand security and regulatory requirements, and obtain necessary approvals for integration.

fields.name: Identify Technical Stack and System Architecture
fields.description: Determine the technologies and system design for integration, ensuring secure API communication, data flow, and compliance with best practices.

fields.name: Step1
fields.description: Contact Mastercard or the relevant provider to request a simulator license and confirm eligibility.

fields.name: Step2
fields.description: Obtain and validate the license key for the testing environment.

fields.name: Step3
fields.description: Activate the license in the simulator and verify access permissions.

fields.name: Step1
fields.description: Initiate communication with eBIRR representatives to request API access and integration guidelines.

fields.name: Step2
fields.description: Review API documentation, authentication mechanisms, and supported transaction types.

fields.name: Step3
fields.description: Understand compliance requirements, including KYC (Know Your Customer), AML (Anti-Money Laundering), and regulatory obligations.

fields.name: Step4
fields.description: Obtain necessary approvals and agreements from eBIRR to proceed with integration.

fields.name: Step1
fields.description: Assess the existing infrastructure and select appropriate technologies for integration (e.g., Django for backend, REST API consumption, MySQL for database).

fields.name: Step2
fields.description: Define the architecture, including API endpoints, middleware, and data flow between eBIRR and the application.

fields.name: Step3
fields.description: Identify security measures such as encryption, tokenization, and authentication strategies.

fields.name: Step4
fields.description: Prepare a high-level system design document for implementation.
